There is a mini how to create [[http://www.minecraft.net/|MineCraft]] server on Debian Lenny.

====== Download ======
In first, download the .jar [[http://www.minecraft.net/download/minecraft_server.jar|here]]

====== Installation ======
Now, you have to install Sun Jvm.

The MineCraft dev notice that its better to use the Sun (proprietary) Jvm.
Add "non-free" on each lines in your **/etc/apt/sources.list** like that :
<code>
deb http://ftp.nerim.net/debian/ lenny main non-free
deb-src http://ftp.nerim.net/debian/ lenny main non-free

deb http://security.debian.org/ lenny/updates main non-free
deb-src http://security.debian.org/ lenny/updates main non-free

deb http://volatile.debian.org/debian-volatile lenny/volatile main non-free
deb-src http://volatile.debian.org/debian-volatile lenny/volatile main non-free
</code>
Update the sources list :
<code>
apt-get update
</code>
And install the Sun Jvm :
<code>
apt-get install sun-java6-jre
</code>

====== Usage ======
I notice you to create a little bash script like that :
<code>
#!/bin/bash

java -Xmx1024M -Xms1024M -jar /root/minecraft/minecraft_server.jar nogui >> /root/minecraft/log_serv 2>&1 &                                   
</code>
And :
<code>
chmod +x your_script.sh
./your_script.sh
</code>
With this little bash script you launch your MineCraft Server with a **log_serv** file with a little histo.

To finish you have to open the 25565 port on your router.
